  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. National level regulations:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key compliance measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Implementing strict identification procedures\n- Maintaining comprehensive financial records\n\n4. Enforcement mechanisms:\n- Criminal penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment for offenders\n\n5. Regulated sectors:\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive legal and regulatory standards across different jurisdictions.",
